@startuml
' @id(SEQ-APPLY-THEME)
' @ref(USE-VIEWER-THEMED)
' @desc(SEQ-APPLY-THEME, "Objective: at MddViewer construction the bundled Inter + JetBrains Mono TTFs are registered via egui's FontDefinitions and installed as the Proportional and Monospace families; then on every frame (update's first call) the OS appearance is queried through dark-light and catppuccin_egui::set_theme is invoked with Mocha (dark) or Latte (light), followed by style overrides for spacing.item_spacing and widget rounding.")
' Objective-side sequence for the Tier-1 theming change: a one-shot
' font registration at startup, then a per-frame OS-appearance probe
' that drives the Catppuccin variant and style tweaks.
title Apply theme (objective)

actor Developer as Dev
participant "eframe runtime" as Eframe
participant "MddViewer::new" as Ctor
participant "MddViewer::update" as Upd
participant "egui::Context" as Ctx
participant "Bundled TTFs\n(Inter, JetBrains Mono)" as Fonts
participant "dark-light\n::detect()" as OsAppearance
participant "catppuccin_egui\n::set_theme" as Catppuccin

Dev -> Eframe : mdd view
Eframe -> Ctor : construct
Ctor -> Fonts : include_bytes!\nInter-Regular.ttf,\nInter-Medium.ttf,\nJetBrainsMono-Regular.ttf
Ctor -> Ctx : set_fonts(FontDefinitions)
note right of Ctx
  Inter → Proportional family,
  JetBrains Mono → Monospace family,
  egui defaults kept as fallback.
end note

== Per-frame chrome refresh ==
Eframe -> Upd : update(ctx, frame)
Upd -> OsAppearance : detect()
OsAppearance --> Upd : Dark | Light | Default
alt OS = Dark or Default
  Upd -> Catppuccin : set_theme(ctx, MOCHA)
else OS = Light
  Upd -> Catppuccin : set_theme(ctx, LATTE)
end
Upd -> Ctx : style_mut().spacing.item_spacing = (8.0, 6.0)\nstyle_mut().visuals.widgets.*.rounding = 6.0
Upd -> Ctx : draw side panels, toolbar, canvas

note right of Catppuccin
  Theme is reapplied each frame so toggling
  the OS appearance live (System Settings →
  Appearance) flips the viewer chrome on the
  next paint without restart.
end note

note over Fonts
  Bundled under crates/mdd-viewer/assets/
  (SIL OFL / Apache-2.0). Adds ≈600 KB to
  the binary; UI text and diff lists become
  legible without depending on system fonts.
end note
@enduml
